sections:
  0. the-quiet-before [36mcinematic[0m/xl  Open on stillness: a single knife on stone, no headline noise — just the object and the promise that this is the story of how it came to exist.
  1. the-smith        [36meditorial[0m/md  Introduce the one maker in Sheffield by name — his workshop, his hands, decades of repetition — establishing origin before any claim is made.
  2. four-days        [36mtimeline[0m/xl  Walk through the four-day process — forging, grinding, heat-treat, handle-fitting — as a sequence of discrete stages, each with its own moment.
  3. the-steel-remembers [36masymmetric[0m/lg  Isolate one fact as the emotional anchor of the page: carbon steel develops a patina and an edge that improves with use, unlike the disposable knives it will replace.
  4. why-it-outlives-you [36mnarrative[0m/md  Address the harder claim directly: this knife is built to be resharpened and repaired for generations, made to be handed down rather than replaced.
  5. the-mark         [36mmodular[0m/sm  Show the maker's stamp on the tang and explain that each knife is individually numbered and dated — proof this is not a batch product.
  6. reserve-yours    [36meditorial[0m/md  Close with quiet invitation — knives are made to order, one smith, limited per month — positioning acquisition as patience rewarded, not urgency manufactured.

